==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[hæft]], Old High German ''heften'' make fast.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːft|-ɑːft]]

===Noun===
'''haft'''

# the [[handle]] of a [[tool]] or [[weapon]]
# {{Northern English dialect}} A piece of [[mountain]] [[pasture]] to which a farm animal has become [[heft]]ed. 

===Alternative spellings===
* [[heft]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# to fit a handle to a tool or weapon.

